---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About | Milly Maker Tracker">
  <main class="page">
    <section class="hero" aria-label="About hero">
      <div class="hero-overlay"></div>

      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-textbox">
          <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
          <h1 class="hero-title">Milly Maker Tracker</h1>
          <p class="hero-sub">
            Milly Maker Tracker is a searchable archive of DraftKings Milly Maker winning lineups and slate results, built for DFS players who want the full record in one place.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="wrap">
      <div class="content">
        <section class="block">
          <h2>What this site does</h2>
          <p>
            Milly Maker Tracker preserves contest results and organizes them so you can actually study them. You can open a slate, see who finished first, view the winning lineup, and review the slate context without chasing screenshots, stale links, or missing pages.
          </p>
          <p>
            Winning lineups are the clearest form of feedback DFS gives you. This site keeps that history in one consistent place so patterns can be reviewed across weeks, slates, and seasons.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="grid">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>What you can learn here</h3>
            <p>
              This site is built for the part of DFS most people skip, the part where you slow down and study what actually won. You can compare roster construction across slates, see how salary was allocated, and review ownership context without relying on memory or guesswork.
            </p>
            <p>
              Over time, the archive becomes a reference point for what tends to repeat, what changes when slate context shifts, and what builds only show up when the game environment forces it.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Why this exists</h3>
            <p>
              Contest history should be easy to access, but it often is not. Even with support involved, requests for past results can require an exact contest, and broad requests can hit limits.
            </p>
            <p>
              This project exists so the history does not depend on one email exchange, one bookmarked page, or one platform decision. The goal is a clean archive that stays available and stays organized.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="block">
          <h2>Why I built it</h2>
          <p>
            I love DFS, and I genuinely enjoy seeing the lineups that win. In a peer to peer game, it is fun to see the usernames at the top, then dig into how the roster got there. Some winning builds feel obvious in hindsight. Other builds look strange until you understand the scoring path and the way the game unfolded.
          </p>
          <p>
            I wanted a place where the record stays clean, where the story of each slate is easy to revisit, and where studying winners feels fun instead of tedious.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="block">
          <h2>What this site is not</h2>
          <p>
            This site does not sell picks, and it does not promise results. It is an archive and an analysis hub meant to support your own process and your own decision making.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="fineprint">
          <h2>Notes and attribution</h2>
          <p>
            DraftKings is a trademark of DraftKings Inc. Milly Maker Tracker is independent and not affiliated with DraftKings.
          </p>
          <p>
            Results are preserved for research and educational use so players can review contest history over time.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page { width: 100%; }

  .hero {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 62vh;
    display: grid;
    align-items: end;

    width: 100vw;
    margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
    margin-right: calc(50% - 50vw);

    background-image: url("/images/about/hero.jpg");
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
  }

  .hero-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
      to bottom,
      rgba(0,0,0,0.20),
      rgba(0,0,0,0.85) 55%,
      rgba(0,0,0,0.94)
    );
  }

  .hero-inner {
    position: relative;
    width: min(1080px, calc(100% - 32px));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 44px 0 56px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.92);
  }

  .hero-textbox {
    display: inline-block;
    max-width: 760px;
    padding: 16px 16px 16px;
    border-radius: 0;
    background: transparent;
    border: 0;
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .hero-title {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 58px);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.96);
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    margin: 14px 0 0;
    max-width: 74ch;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.80);
  }

  .wrap {
    width: min(1080px, calc(100% - 32px));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 44px 0 68px;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    background: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
    outline: 0;
  }

  .wrap::before,
  .wrap::after {
    content: none;
  }

  .content {
    display: grid;
    gap: 28px;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    background: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
    outline: 0;
  }

  .content::before,
  .content::after {
    content: none;
  }

  .block {
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  .block h2 {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    font-size: 22px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.92);
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .block p {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
  }

  .block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    background: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
    outline: 0;
  }

  .grid::before,
  .grid::after {
    content: none;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }

  .card {
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  .card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    font-size: 18px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.92);
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .card p {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
  }

  .card p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .fineprint {
    padding: 0;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    background: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  .fineprint h2 {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    font-size: 18px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.92);
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .fineprint p {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
  }

  .fineprint p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
</style>
